uk.co.strangeskies.mathematics.expression

Interface Variable<S extends Variable<S>>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - See Self for more information. This must be self-bounding as the value of the expression is the variable itself.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Copyable<S>, Expression<S>, Observable<Expression<S>>, Self<S>

    public interface Variable<S extends Variable<S>>
extends Expression<S>, Self<S>
    A variable for use in reactive programming. A Variable in this sense is a first class expression, that is to say it is an expression whose value is itself.
